<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 1672/2000 amending Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999 establishing a support system for producers of certain arable crops, to include flax and hemp grown for fibre of 27 July 2000 </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1672/2000, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999, millega kehtestatakse teatavate p&otilde;llukultuuride tootjatele toetuss&uuml;steem, et h&otilde;lmata kiu tootmiseks kasvatatav lina ja kanep 27. juuli 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 36 and 37 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikleid 36 ja 37, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Committee of the Regions(4), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse regioonide komitee arvamust (4) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) The common agricultural policy aims to attain the objectives referred to in the Treaty, taking account of the market situation. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) &Uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika taotlus on saavutada asutamislepingus nimetatud eesm&auml;rgid, v&otilde;ttes arvesse turuolukorda. </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The flax and hemp sector has undergone profound changes since the entry into force of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70 of 29 June 1970 on the common organisation of the market in flax and hemp(5). </inglise>
<eesti> 2) Lina- ja kanepisektor on alates n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 (lina- ja kanepituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta) (5) j&otilde;ustumisest p&otilde;hjalikult muutunud. </eesti>
<inglise> In addition to the traditional production of long flax fibre for textiles and the traditional uses of hemp fibres, flax and hemp are now also being grown for a new market in short fibres. </inglise>
<eesti> Lisaks tavap&auml;rasele pika linakiu tekstiilmaterjaliks tootmisele ja kanepikiudude tavap&auml;rastele kasutusaladele kasvatatakse lina ja kanepit t&auml;nap&auml;eval ka uue l&uuml;hikeste kiudude turu tarbeks. </eesti>
<inglise> Since these short fibres can be used for new materials, their production should be encouraged in order also to promote innovative markets offering a future. </inglise>
<eesti> Kuna neid l&uuml;hikesi kiude saab kasutada uutes materjalides, tuleks nende tootmist soodustada, et edendada ka uuenduslikke tuleviku turge. </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Given its attractiveness, the aid provided for in Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70 has given rise, in some Member States, to purely speculative production. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Oma atraktiivsuse t&otilde;ttu on m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 etten&auml;htud abi m&otilde;ningates liikmesriikides kaasa toonud &uuml;ksnes spekulatiivse tootmise. </eesti>
<inglise> Steps taken to combat this phenomenon have further complicated the legislation governing this sector and have not always had the desired success. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle n&auml;htuse vastu v&otilde;itlemiseks v&otilde;etud abin&otilde;ud on muutnud k&otilde;nealust sektorit reguleerivad &otilde;igusaktid keerulisemaks ega ole alati saavutanud soovitud edu. </eesti>
<inglise> (4) In order to solve the problems facing the market in flax and hemp grown for fibre, the amount of aid granted to the growers concerned should be comparable to that for competitor crops. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) Kiu tootmiseks kasvatatava lina ja kanepi turuga seotud probleemide lahendamiseks peaks kasvatajatele antava toetuse suurus olema v&otilde;rreldav konkureerivatele p&otilde;llukultuuridele antava toetusega. </eesti>
<inglise> To that end, and with a view to simplifying the applicable legislation, these crops should be included in the support system for producers of certain arable crops established by Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999(6). </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks tuleks need p&otilde;llukultuurid, pidades silmas kohaldatavate &otilde;igusaktide lihtsustamist, l&uuml;litada m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 (6) kehtestatud teatavate p&otilde;llukultuuride tootjate toetuss&uuml;steemi. </eesti>
<inglise> Moreover, where there is a need to ensure continued production, Council Regulation (EC) No 1673/2000 of 27 July 2000 on the common organisation of the market in flax and hemp grown for fibre(7) provides for aid for processing flax and hemp straw. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootmise j&auml;tkumise tagamiseks on n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuli 2000. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1673/2000 (kiu tootmiseks kasvatatava lina ja kanepi turu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta) (7) ette n&auml;htud toetus lina- ja kanepivarte t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Aid for processing should lead to an increase in the purchase price of flax and hemp straw and make production more profitable for producers. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;tlemistoetus peaks kaasa tooma lina- ja kanepivarte ostuhinna t&otilde;usu ja muutma tootmise tootjatele tulutoovamaks. </eesti>
<inglise> (5) To ensure a smooth transition to the level of support granted for cereals and to solve the current problems caused by the existence of different aid schemes for fibre flax and seed flax, the payments for flax and hemp grown for fibre should be the same as those granted for linseed, which must themselves be aligned with those for cereals by the 2002/2003 marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) Ladusa &uuml;lemineku tagamiseks teraviljale m&auml;&auml;ratud toetuse tasemele ning kiulina ja seemnelina eri abikavade p&otilde;hjustatud probleemide lahendamiseks peaksid kiu tootmiseks kasvatatavale linale ja kanepile makstavad summad olema v&otilde;rdsed linaseemnele makstavate summadega, mis tuleb omakorda vastavusse viia 2002/2003. turustusaastal teraviljale makstavate summadega. </eesti>
<inglise> Additional aid in Finland and Sweden, as envisaged for competing crops in Article 4 of Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999, is also justified in the case of flax and hemp. </inglise>
<eesti> Lina ja kanepi puhul on Soomel ja Rootsil &otilde;igus t&auml;iendavale abile, nagu on ette n&auml;htud m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 artiklis 4 konkureerivate p&otilde;llukultuuride puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> (6) To take account of the recent establishment of flax and hemp production in particular near processing plants, eligibility for the scheme laid down in Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999 should be extended to cover the areas and crops in question. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Et v&otilde;tta arvesse lina ja kanepi kasvatamise uudsust, eriti t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;tete &uuml;mbruses, tuleks laiendada m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 etten&auml;htud kava tingimusi, et see h&otilde;lmaks ka k&otilde;nealuseid piirkondi ja p&otilde;llukultuure. </eesti>
<inglise> (7) To avert the danger that the aims of Regulation (EC) No 1251/1999 might be circumvented, the granting of the per-hectare aid for flax and hemp grown for fibre should be made subject to certain conditions as regards cultivation. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1251/1999 eesm&auml;rkide eiramise ohu v&auml;ltimiseks peaks kiu tootmiseks kasvatatavale linale ja kanepile m&auml;&auml;ratav hektaritoetus s&otilde;ltuma teatavatest kasvatamisega seotud tingimustest. </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Specific measures should be laid down for hemp, to ensure that illegal crops cannot be hidden among the crops eligible for area payments, thereby disturbing the common market organisation for hemp. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) Kanepi puhul tuleks ette n&auml;ha erimeetmed tagamaks, et pindalatoetuse tingimustele vastavate p&otilde;llukultuuride hulka ei saaks peita ebaseaduslikke p&otilde;llukultuure, mis h&auml;iriksid kanepituru &uuml;hist korraldust. </eesti>
<inglise> Provision must therefore be made for area payments to be granted only for areas sown to varieties of hemp offering certain guarantees with regard to the psychotropic substance content. </inglise>
<eesti> Seep&auml;rast tuleb ette n&auml;ha, et pindalatoetusi m&auml;&auml;ratakse ainult sellistele piirkondadele, kus k&uuml;lvatud kanepisortide puhul on olemas kindlad garantiid uimastava toimega ainete sisalduse suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> (9) In order that the quantities eligible for straw-processing aid under Regulation (EC) No 1673/2000 can be monitored, straw production must be linked to the area on which it is grown and producers should have imposed on them obligations which are reciprocal to those imposed on the producers involved, </inglise>
<eesti> 9) Selleks et kontrollida koguseid, millele v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 1673/2000 kohaselt varte t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise toetust m&auml;&auml;rata, peab varte tootmine olema seotud piirkonnaga, kus neid kasvatatakse, ja tootjatel peaksid olema asjaomaste tootjatega v&otilde;rdsed kohustused, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
